SIMPLE: poison_bush
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poison bush
<hw>Poison bush</hw>. <mark>In Australia:</mark> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any
fabaceous shrub of the genus <gen>Gastrolobium</gen>, the herbage of
which is poisonous to stock; also, any species of several related
genera, as <gen>Oxylobium</gen>, <gen>Gompholobium</gen>, etc.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The plant <spn>Myoporum deserti</spn>, often
distinguished as <altname>Ellangowan poison bush</altname> or
<altname>dogwood poison bush</altname>.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The
ulmaceous plant <spn>Trema cannabina</spn>, which, though not poisonous,
is injurious to stock because of its large amount of fiber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poison cup</ent>⟦br⟧
